<paragraph id="93E1793CFAC50D969208419EBFA7B9A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="827F2EA556D0A60C95A745BD25C865DF" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName id="31988D1FC8698BD9E35138D493DD27A3" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium japonicum" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="japonicum">Microthecium japonicum</taxonomicName>
is characterized by ostiolate ascomata and ellipsoidal to fusiform, punctate-reticulate ascospores, similar to 
<taxonomicName id="C4B0BB1A113374E8EFF38550D840BC32" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. moureai" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="moureai">Mi. moureai</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName id="0E042473AC608C41BB3F4BE69BC5BDBB" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. japonicum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="japonicum">Mi. japonicum</taxonomicName>
produces a phialidic asexual morph and bulbils (absent in 
<taxonomicName id="34DBC032D056D9C71E938D92C907741C" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. moureai" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="moureai">Mi. moureai</taxonomicName>
) and delicately reticulate ascospores (coarsely reticulate in 
<taxonomicName id="70650CE964742277ED4EB617B7AAD9F6" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. moureai" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="moureai">Mi. moureai</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
